<font color="#FF0000">RESPONSES </font><br>
<tt>Sat Sep  6  8:51:50 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
This is going to capture everybody, I hope.<br><br>
Silent Warrior, it is true that I may be further down the road but it is the same road that we all are on.  I don't pretend to have any answers but maybe advice (mine and others) may give a view that helps resolve issues.  Looking at a knot from a different angle may provide the means to untangle it.  I do not expect or want soul baring issues to be put up here for the world to see.  But working through the things that we do every day and having an outlet to vent may, just may, provide insight that advances healing. I am no expert on anything, except teaching techs how to fix copier machines, but I have walked the road.  Not to it's end.  The journey is still in progress.  I feel anger, frustration,pain and heartache but it is an emotion that is there then passes.  I was told that I had no &quot;grays&quot; in my world.  Everything was black and white.  Healing puts grays into our lives.<br><br>
Cook, I hope that grays come into your life.  My God, is it any wonder that you respond to the things that you do, the way that you do?  Peoples lives, even today, depend on your split second decisions. Being a grunt, those decisions save or cost lives in you squad.  Today, as a police officer, decisions may cost you; civilians, your partner, and brother officers their lives. These parameters allow little or no space to change the survival skill that were learned in Vietnam and on the streets into coping skills for todays societal interaction. You are someone that I have always wanted to be.  A peace officer.  A warrior who remembers his friends of combat.  Cook, write your book.  Like Ed has said, it puts things to bed and shoves reality in your face.  Once this is done maybe you can have some peace.<br><br>
Ed, I love your sense of humor!  For so long it was so serious that no one could crack a joke on this site. Everthing was heavy duty.  That is why a thread was started, just to vent the humor.  You are my brother in arms.  We old farts have to have a sense of humor because the older we get the funnier the world seems to us.  I feel honored to talk to and get a response from someone who is as involved as you are with vets.  I don't or can't or won't let that into my life.  Helping others is healing. Sharing is healing.  I post my senses and feelings here.  I am not a professional anything.  Except maybe husband, grasscutter, honey-do fixer, vet.  My, doesn't the list grow when you start them?<br>
Do not apologise for how you express your feelings.  Many time I used anger to express mine.  I thought that humor was there but found out it was hurtful saracasm.  So now I just go eat a can of Spam and a jar of Mayonaise when I piss someone off.  Drive on!<br><br>
John,  having graduated from high school in Portland, I envy you sometimes living in the Beaver State.  But, it is said that Virginia is prettier.  Congrats on the test score.  It is difficult to concentrate when you life is in turmoil.  But thanks,bud, for keeping us posted.<br><br>
Tom, I guess the site is always on track.  It sometimes takes us where we don't want to go but then that is what makes this place so uniques.  I missed all the guys who used to post here, but I also enjoy the &quot;new&quot; guys and the different tracks that they have laid down.<br><br>
So, I don't pretend or want anyone to think that I am cured of all this crap.  Because I still get tweaked and lash out at people and things.  I have been told that I handle it &quot;a little better&quot; than I used to.  But folks, we (for the most part) are getting to the point where this stress and tension is not good for our minds and it sure is killing our bodies. <br><br>
I am now lost for words.  I don't want anyone to think that I can lead them to happiness and resovle all their problem.  Christ, I have enough of my own to deal with.  I am just proposing a refocus of what we do here on the site.  We don't need a new thread, a new title, a reason.  Just start anywhere.  Make comments, state issues, post hurts, e-mail feelings.  <br><br>
Wow, guess I had words left.  So, I'm trying to get rid of my Netscape and switch to Explorer without losing all my data files and I'm getting pissed. So my brothers,later...<br>
Chet<br>
Rvn 65-67<br>
 
